/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:642:`Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader` loads image data asynchronously for dali-ui apps, while `Dali::Ui::ImageUrl` turns an encoded image buffer into a URL-style handle that can be passed through image-oriented code.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:649:- [Use ImageUrl for Encoded Image Buffers](#use-imageurl-for-encoded-image-buffers)
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:654:In a dali-ui application, screen code should keep the app-facing model in terms of `Dali::Ui::View`. `Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader` is not itself a view; it is a helper object used by view controllers or image-related services when image decoding should run asynchronously.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:656:Create the loader with `Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader::New`, then call `Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader::Load` with a URL and requested `ImageDimensions`. The returned task id identifies that single load request.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:663:  : mLoader(Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader::New())
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:667:  uint32_t RequestImage(const Dali::String& url, ImageDimensions dimensions)
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:673:  Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader mLoader;
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:677:Use this pattern when a `Dali::Ui::View`-based screen needs decoded image data before updating an image view, cache, or model object. The view tree remains owned by your screen code; `Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader` only owns the asynchronous loading work.
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-guide_auto/cache/generation/cli_raw/image-loader.stderr:681:Each call to `Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader::Load` returns a `uint32_t` loading task id. Store that id when the result is still relevant to the current screen state. If the user navigates away, changes the requested image, or closes the image panel, cancel the stale request with `Dali::Ui::AsyncImageLoader::Cancel`.
